    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-01-10T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-01-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="767"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/960: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-10T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 10, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. Reference Shanghai’s 15, January 6, 2 p.m., in regard to Japanese
                    interference, in the matter of an appointment, with the administration of the
                    Chinese Maritime Customs.</p>
                <p>If the approach made by the American Consul General at Shanghai proves not
                    effective the Department desires that, unless you perceive <pb facs="0725"
                        n="717" xml:id="pg_717"/> objection, you approach the Japanese Foreign
                    Office along the lines of the second paragraph of the telegram under
                    reference.</p>
                <p>Shanghai should continue to keep the Department and you informed of any
                    developments in the matter.</p>
                <p>Sent to Tokyo via Shanghai. Repeated to Peiping and Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
